0their%20experiences%20on%20the%20warehouse%20floor%20to%20%26quot%3Bslavery.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BAmazon%20has%20been%20a%20pioneer%20in%20the%20area%20of%20worker%20surveillance%20and%20management%20in%20its%20warehouses%2C%20and%20Walmart%2C%20long%20known%20for%20adopting%20repressive%20practices%20to%20monitor%20workers%2C%20is%20also%20entering%20a%20new%20phase%20of%20accelerated%20technology%20deployment%20across%20its%20facilities%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20report%20says.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EData%20from%20two%20recent%20surveys%2C%20funded%20in%20part%20by%20Oxfam%20%E2%80%94%20the%20National%20Survey%20of%20Amazon%20Warehouse%20Workers%20and%20the%20National%20Survey%20of%20Walmart%20Warehouse%20Workers%20%E2%80%94%20is%20included%20in%20the%20report.%20The%20results%20show%20that%20a%20substantial%20amount%20of%20Amazon%20and%20Walmart%20warehouse%20employees%20surveyed%20reported%20being%20closely%20watched%20by%20technology%20while%20in%20the%20workplace.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BAs%20the%20data%20shows%2C%20although%20key%20differences%20exist%2C%20workers%20at%20both%20Amazon%20and%20Walmart%20are%20experiencing%20concerning%20levels%20of%20surveillance%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20report%20says.%20%26quot%3BCrucially%2C%20excessive%20surveillance%20is%20not%20simply%20disconcerting%20for%20workers%3B%20it%20also%20erodes%20worker%20rights.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%225500%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Amazon%20packages%20on%20a%20conveyor%20belt.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F64b831dca46ce30019a1d0df%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%223864%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EPackages%20are%20transported%20on%20a%20conveyor%20belt%20an%20Amazon%20warehouse%2C%20busy%20on%20Prime%20Day%20on%20July%2011%2C%202023%3Cp%3ESoren%20Larson%2FReuters%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Ch2%3EAmazon%20and%20Walmart%20slammed%20Oxfam's%20report%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EAmazon%20has%20disputed%20claims%20that%20it%20uses%20technology%20to%20monitor%20its%20warehouse%20workers%2C%20while%20Walmart%20said%20the%20report%20fails%20to%20accurately%20depict%20the%20company's%20use%20of%20technology.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWhile%20we%20respect%20Oxfam%20and%20its%20mission%2C%20we%20have%20strong%20disagreements%20with%20the%20characterizations%20and%20conclusions%20made%20throughout%20this%20paper%20%E2%80%94%20many%20based%20on%20flawed%20methodology%20and%20hyperbolic%20anecdotes%2C%26quot%3B%20Amazon%20spokesperson%20Maureen%20Lynch%20Vogel%20told%20Business%20Insider%20in%20a%20statement.%20%26quot%3BIn%20reality%2C%20Amazon%20has%20made%20notable%20safety%20gains%20and%20enriched%20the%20communities%20in%20which%20we%20operate%2C%20providing%20safe%2C%20good%20paying%20jobs%20with%20health%20benefits%20and%20educational%20opportunities.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EVogel%20went%20on%20to%20attack%20the%20research%20itself.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BTraditionally%2C%20researchers%20work%20to%20disprove%20pre-existing%20beliefs%20and%20biases%2C%20but%20the%20organizations%20involved%20in%20this%20paper%20did%20the%20opposite%20%E2%80%94%20they%20started%20with%20biases%20and%20sought%20to%20prove%20them%20%E2%80%94%20which%20is%20disappointing%2C%26quot%3B%20Vogel%20said.%20%26quot%3BWe're%20not%20perfect%2C%20but%20we're%20making%20measurable%20progress%20and%20our%20employees'%20health%2C%20safety%2C%20and%20well-being%20will%20always%20be%20our%20top%20priority.%26quot%3B%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20Walmart%20spokesperson%20told%20BI%20in%20a%20statement%3A%20%26quot%3BOxfam's%20claims%20are%20based%20on%20incomplete%20and%20misleading%20information.%20This%20report%20inaccurately%20represents%20Walmart's%20use%20of%20technology%20and%20Walmart's%20publicly%20available%20disclosures%20around%20data%20privacy%20and%20worker%20safety.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20the%20data%20outlined%20in%20the%20Oxfam%20report%2C%2077%25%20of%20Amazon%20warehouse%20workers%20surveyed%20and%2062%25%20of%20Walmart%20warehouse%20employees%20who%20participated%20reported%20that%20%26quot%3Btechnology%20can%20tell%26quot%3B%20if%20they%20are%20%26quot%3Bactively%20engaged%26quot%3B%20in%20their%20work%20almost%20or%20most%20of%20the%20time.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESimilarly%2C%2072%25%20of%20Amazon%20warehouse%20employees%20who%20participated%20and%2067%25%20of%20Walmart%20warehouse%20employees%20surveyed%20reported%20that%20%26quot%3Bhow%20fast%26quot%3B%20they%20work%20is%20measured%20by%20company%20technology%20always%20or%20most%20of%20the%20time%2C%20the%20data%20in%20the%20report%20shows.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20a%20seven-page%20response%20to%20Oxfam%20viewed%20by%20BI%2C%20Tessie%20Petion%2C%20the%20head%20of%20ESG%20Engagement%20at%20Amazon%2C%20wrote%20that%20Oxfam's%20report%20%26quot%3Billustrates%20a%20misunderstanding%20of%20what%20the%20technology%20in%20our%20facilities%20does%20and%20doesn't%20do.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20do%20use%20technology%20in%20our%20facilities%20to%20help%20ensure%20the%20safety%20and%20security%20of%20our%20employees%20%E2%80%94%20it%20would%20be%20irresponsible%20if%20we%20did%20not%20take%20this%20approach.%20We%20also%20secure%20our%20inventory.%20Our%20facilities%20house%20hundreds%20of%20thousands%20of%20products%20that%20will%20be%20shipped%20to%20customers%20around%20the%20world%2C%20and%20the%20technology%20in%20our%20facilities%20helps%20guide%20the%20flow%20of%20goods%20through%20the%20sites%2C%26quot%3B%20Petion%20wrote.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPetion%20continued%2C%20%26quot%3BThis%20is%20similar%20to%20technology%20used%20throughout%20the%20industry.%20We%20do%20not%20use%20the%20camera%20technology%20in%20our%20warehouses%20to%20monitor%20employees.%20Employees%20who%20have%20questions%20about%20how%20our%20technology%20works%2C%20or%20concerns%20about%20the%20data%20it%20collects%2C%20are%20always%20encouraged%20to%20speak%20to%20their%20manager%20who%20can%20explain%20it%20to%20them%20in%20greater%20detail.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221000%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Walmart%20warehouse%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F5e78aa822d654f7f1372fe22%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22667%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EInside%20of%20a%20Walmart%20warehouse.%3Cp%3ESuzanne%20Kreiter%2FThe%20Boston%20Globe%20via%20Getty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Ch2%3EMore%20than%20half%20of%20Amazon%20and%20Walmart%20employees%20surveyed%20find%20it%20tough%20to%20get%20to%20the%20bathroom%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20data%20in%20Oxfam's%20report%2C%20roughly%20three-quarters%20of%20both%20Amazon%20and%20Walmart%20warehouse%20workers%20surveyed%20reported%20feeling%20pressure%20to%20work%20faster%20at%20least%20some%20of%20the%20time.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BBeing%20monitored%20this%20minutely%20takes%20a%20physical%20and%20mental%20toll%20as%20workers%20need%20to%20make%20decisions%20about%20taking%20breaks%2C%20eating%2C%20going%20to%20the%20bathroom%2C%20or%20even%20drinking%20water%20with%20their%20pace%20or%20performance%20metrics%20in%20mind%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20report%20says.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESome%2054%25%20of%20Amazon%20respondents%20and%2057%25%20of%20Walmart%20respondents%20reported%20that%20their%20production%20rate%20makes%20it%20hard%20for%20them%20to%20use%20the%20bathroom%20at%20least%20some%20of%20the%20time%2C%20data%20included%20in%20the%20report%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20conditions%20there%20are%20absolutely%20horrific%2C%26quot%3B%20one%20Amazon%20warehouse%20worker%20in%20Alabama%20was%20quoted%20as%20saying%20in%20the%20report.%20%26quot%3BI%20likened%20it%20to%20slavery%2C%20because%20they%20care%20more%20about%20quotas%20and%20meeting%20production%20rates%20than%20actually%20caring%20about%20us%20as%20human%20beings%20inside%20there.%20I%20feel%20more%20like%20a%20number.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPetion%2C%20in%20her%20response%20to%20Oxfam%2C%20called%20the%20assertion%20that%20workers%20don't%20get%20sufficient%20breaks%20%26quot%3Bwrong.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIn%20addition%20to%20their%20regularly%20scheduled%20breaks%2C%20employees%20are%20free%20to%20take%20informal%20breaks%20throughout%20their%20shifts%20to%20use%20the%20restroom%2C%20get%20water%2C%20or%20talk%20to%20a%20manager%20or%20HR%2C%26quot%3B%20Petion%20wrote.%20%26quot%3BIf%20there's%20ever%20a%20concern%20about%20a%20manager%20misusing%20productivity%20guidance%20or%20asking%20employees%20to%20prioritize%20productivity%20over%20safety%2C%20we%20immediately%20investigate%20and%20take%20appropriate%20action.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EThe%20data%20shows%20a%20move%20towards%20a%20'really%20dystopian%20workplace%2C'%20Oxfam%20director%20says%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EIrit%20Tamir%2C%20the%20director%20of%20Oxfam%20America's%20private%20sector%20department%2C%20told%20BI%20that%20the%20research%20outlined%20in%20the%20report%20shows%20a%20move%20towards%20a%20%26quot%3Breally%20dystopian%20workplace%20where%20people%20feel%20like%20they're%20constantly%20being%20monitored%20and%20watched.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThey%20are%20feeling%20oppressed%20by%20this%20cognitive%20tax%20on%20workers%20who%20fear%20this%20constant%20surveillance%20and%20punishment%26quot%3B%20for%20taking%20breaks%2C%20Tamir%20said.%20%26quot%3BAnd%20as%20a%20result%2C%20you%20know%2C%20I%20think%20these%20warehouse%20floors%20have%20become%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwarehouse-injuries-amazon-chronic-pain-speed-risk-productivity-targets-employees-2022-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eincubators%20of%20injury%3C%2Fa%3E%20sustained%20by%20automation%20and%20surveillance%2C%20and%20workplace%20cultures%20of%20intimidation.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Oxfam%20report%20says%20that%20at%20Amazon%2C%20warehouse%20workers%20%26quot%3Bare%20assigned%20handheld%20devices%20or%20scanners%20that%20record%2C%20count%2C%20and%20measure%20every%20item%20they%20move%20during%20their%20day.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThese%20systems%20measure%20down%20to%20the%20second%20the%20amount%20of%20time%20a%20worker%20spends%20not%20actively%20sorting%2C%20packing%2C%20or%20performing%20work%20%E2%80%94%20what%20is%20called%20'time%20off%20task%2C'%26quot%3B%20the%20report%20says.%20Those%20scanners%2C%20according%20to%20the%20report%2C%20%26quot%3Bplay%20a%20key%20role%20in%20the%20surveillance%20machine%26quot%3B%20because%20it%20says%20it%20can%20lead%20to%20automated%20penalties%20for%20workers%20who%20fail%20to%20meet%20production%20targets.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIn%20addition%2C%20hundreds%20of%20security%20cameras%20are%20constantly%20monitoring%20the%20warehouse%20floor%2C%20ready%20to%20notify%20a%20manager%20when%20a%20worker%20is%20away%20from%20their%20station%20for%20too%20long%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20report%20says.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%22842%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22walmart%20warehouse%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F52164881eab8ea8e51000004%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22564%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EOxfam's%20report%20says%20%26quot%3Blittle%20is%20known%26quot%3B%20about%20the%20technology%20Walmart%20uses%20in%20its%20warehouses.%20%3Cp%3Ecorporate.walmart.com%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20it%20comes%20to%20Walmart%2C%20the%20report%20says%20that%20%26quot%3Blittle%20is%20known%20about%20the%20technology%20the%20company%20is%20currently%20using%20to%20monitor%20workers%20across%20its%20warehouses%2C%26quot%3B%20but%20states%20that%20workers%20it%20surveyed%20reported%20being%20%26quot%3Bwatched%20constantly.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20report%20says%20that%20the%20data%20from%20the%20Walmart%20warehouse%20worker%20survey%20analyzed%20in%20the%20report%20is%20the%20%26quot%3Bfirst%20of%20its%20kind%20to%20offer%20insights%20into%20the%20extent%20of%20worker%20monitoring%20a