nts%20ranging%20from%20three%20months%20to%20a%20year.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAmenities%20in%20its%20houses%20include%20gyms%20and%20lounges%2C%20and%20residents%20can%20gain%20access%20to%20in-house%20entertainment%20like%20parties%2C%20monthly%20catered%20breakfasts%2C%20and%20excursions.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3EThere%20are%2014%20Cohabs%20houses%20in%20NYC%2C%20with%20five%20more%20expected%20to%20open%20in%20the%20next%20four%20months.%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221137%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22The%20location%20in%20Harlem%20is%20the%20biggest%20in%20the%20US%20so%20far.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F65fc4b074af076d3cf925df9%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22853%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EA%20lounge%20area%20in%20a%20Harlem%20Cohabs%20location.%3Cp%3EPierre%20Jampy%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3ECohabs%20has%20around%20250%20members%20%E2%80%94%20whom%20the%20company%20calls%20residents%20%E2%80%94%20across%20its%2014%20locations%20in%20NYC.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20Dan%20Clark%2C%20the%20director%20of%20Cohabs%20in%20the%20US%2C%20the%20number%20of%20US%20members%20is%20set%20to%20grow%20to%20400%20by%20the%20end%20of%202024%20as%20the%20company%20plans%20to%20expand%20in%20New%20York.%20It%20is%20opening%20a%20location%20in%20Washington%2C%20D.C.%2C%20and%20eyeing%20Chicago%20for%20another%20one.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3EOne%20of%20Cohabs'%20largest%20US%20homes%20is%20in%20Harlem%2C%20with%2028%20%26quot%3Broommates%26quot%3B%20over%20five%20floors.%20%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222533%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22The%20exterior%20facade%20of%20the%20Cohabs%20location%20in%20Harlem.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F65fc4afe895d82203032f1d1%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221900%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EThe%20exterior%20facade%20of%20the%20Cohabs%20location%20in%20Harlem.%3Cp%3EPierre%20Jampy%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20of%20April%2C%20Cohabs'%20location%20in%20Harlem%20is%20one%20of%20its%20biggest%20in%20the%20US.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20building%20was%20dilapidated%20for%20years%20until%20Cohabs%20bought%20and%20renovated%20it%2C%20Clark%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENow%20the%20building%20is%20home%20to%2028%20adults%2C%20ranging%20in%20age%20from%2023%20to%2036.%20To%20live%20there%20or%20at%20any%20Cohabs%20house%2C%20prospective%20members%20submit%20an%20application%20through%20the%20website%2C%20undergo%20background%20checks%2C%20and%20get%20interviewed%2C%20Clark%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EClark%20said%20his%20team%20and%20current%20residents%20give%20prospective%20residents%20tours%20of%20the%20homes%2C%20which%20not%20all%20coliving%20companies%20do%20as%20they%20aren't%20always%20physically%20%26quot%3Bstaffed%26quot%3B%20with%20employees%20on%20site.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3ERent%20for%20a%20room%20at%20Cohabs'%20Harlem%20house%20ranges%20from%20%241%2C700%20a%20month%20to%20%242%2C700%20a%20month.%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221280%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20single%20room%20in%20Cohabs'%20house%20in%20Harlem.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F65f9fc75895d82203032653e%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22960%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EA%20single%20room%20in%20the%20Harlem%20house%2C%20which%20ranges%20in%20size%20from%2074%20to%20160%20square%20feet%2C%20starts%20at%20%241%2C700%20a%20month.%3Cp%3EMaria%20Noyen%2FBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3ERent%20depends%20on%20the%20location%20and%20type%20of%20accommodation%20members%20choose.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20Harlem%2C%20prices%20start%20at%20%241%2C700%20a%20month%20for%20a%20room%20that%20is%2074%20to%20160%20square%20feet%20and%20go%20up%20to%20%242%2C700%20a%20month%20for%20a%20room%20that%20is%20200%20square%20feet.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt's%20the%20prices%20that%20have%20caused%20a%20stir%20on%20social%20media.%20After%20Wolf%2C%20a%20member%20living%20in%20a%20Cohabs%20location%20in%20Brooklyn%20posted%20about%20her%20experience%20on%20TikTok.%20Her%20video%20received%20a%20wave%20of%20responses%20from%20people%20confused%20as%20to%20why%20members%20would%20pay%20thousands%20for%20relatively%20small%20rooms.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ECohabs%20member%20Elisa%2C%20who%20asked%20to%20be%20referred%20to%20by%20her%20first%20name%20for%20privacy%20reasons%2C%20told%20Business%20Insider%20that%20critics%20don't%20see%20how%20she%20and%20her%20housemates%20are%20paying%20for%20more%20than%20square%20footage.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETheir%20rent%20covers%20furnished%20private%20bedrooms%2C%20utilities%20like%20WiFi%20and%20electricity%2C%20maintenance%20requests%2C%20and%20access%20to%20shared%20spaces%20like%20the%20gym.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EElisa%2C%20a%2030-year-old%20business%20developer%20at%20a%20startup%2C%20pays%20around%20%242%2C000%20a%20month%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Efor%20a%20135-square-foot%20room%20in%20another%20Cohabs%20house%20in%20Harlem.%20She%20often%20stops%20by%20other%20Cohabs%20locations%2C%20including%20the%20bigger%20Harlem%20one%2C%20to%20visit%20friends.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BFor%20this%20amount%2C%20I'm%20also%20paying%20for%20common%20spaces%20and%20the%20fact%20that%20their%20team%20is%20doing%20an%20amazing%20job%20at%20bringing%20a%20premium%20service%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMeanwhile%2C%20Clark%20said%20the%20blowback%20Cohabs%20received%20on%20social%20media%20comes%20down%20to%20%26quot%3Ba%20lack%20of%20knowledge%26quot%3B%20from%20those%20unfamiliar%20with%20the%20concept%20and%20the%20other%20facilities%20residents%20can%20access.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAt%20the%20same%20time%2C%20he%20acknowledged%20that%20coliving%20isn't%20for%20everyone%2C%20so%20members%20can%20give%2060%20days'%20notice%20if%20they%20decide%20to%20move%20out%20before%20their%20agreed-upon%20term.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIf%20you%20don't%20like%20it%2C%20this%20is%20coliving.%20We%20don't%20want%20you%20to%20be%20miserable%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3ECommon%20areas%20include%20a%20large%20ground-floor%20kitchen%2C%20a%20gym%2C%20and%20three%20outdoor%20decks.%20%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222533%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22The%20gym%20is%20rarely%20crowded%2C%20residents%20say.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F65fc4aed4af076d3cf925de0%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221900%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EThe%20gym%20is%20rarely%20crowded%2C%20residents%20say.%3Cp%3EPierre%20Jampy%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EMost%20communal%20spaces%20in%20the%20Harlem%20Cohabs%20house%20are%20in%20the%20basement%2C%20including%20the%20large%20kitchen%2C%20several%20lounges%2C%20and%20the%20gym.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDespite%20having%20to%20share%20with%20nearly%2030%20roommates%2C%20Cohabs%20member%20Greg%20Rayon%20said%20he%20rarely%20finds%20the%20gym%20too%20busy%20for%20use.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI've%20never%20had%20the%20occasion%20where%20I%20go%20in%20and%20there's%20no%20space%2C%26quot%3B%20Rayon%2C%2036%2C%20said.%20%26quot%3BPeople%20do%20different%20things.%26quot%3B%20It%20also%20helps%20that%20you%20eventually%20end%20up%20%26quot%3Bfiguring%20out%20people's%20routines%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20added.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3EThere's%20also%20a%20TV%20lounge%20where%20the%20roommates%20have%20organized%20viewing%20parties.%20%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222533%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22The%20shared%20TV%20lounge.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F65fc4ae12417f97b87ce0b7b%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221900%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EThe%20shared%20TV%20lounge.%3Cp%3EPierre%20Jampy%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3ESteps%20away%20from%20the%20gym%20and%20basement%20kitchen%20is%20a%20lounge%20fitted%20with%20large%20L-shaped%20sofas%2C%20rugs%2C%20coffee%20tables%2C%20and%20a%20big%20TV.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt's%20near%20impossible%20to%20find%20something%20that%20all%2028%20roommates%20like%20to%20watch%2C%20as%20well%20as%20organize%20a%20time%20that%20everyone%20is%20free%2C%20but%20Elisa%20said%20at%20least%20a%20dozen%20people%20have%20managed%20to%20fit%20for%20past%20screenings.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20basement%20is%20where%20most%20residents%20hang%20out%20when%20they%20want%20to%20socialize%2C%20said%20Y%C3%A4elle%20De%20Vroey%2C%20a%20resident%20of%20the%20Harlem%20house%20who%20also%20works%20for%20Cohabs%20as%20a%20designer%20curating%20furniture%20and%20interior%20decor.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BOn%20weekends%2C%20it's%20amazing%2C%26quot%3B%20De%20Vroey%2C%2024%2C%20said%20of%20the%20parties%2C%20group%20dinners%2C%20and%20other%20activities.%20%26quot%3BThere's%20always%20something%20happening%20here.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3EUpstairs%2C%20accommodations%20are%20divided%20into%20four%20%26quot%3Bunits%2C%26quot%3B%20which%20act%20like%20distinct%20apartments.%20%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221280%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22In%20Unit%202%2C%20residents%20keep%20track%20of%20their%20birthdays%20on%20a%20large%20chalkboard.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F65fc4abf2417f97b87ce0b57%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22960%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EIn%20Unit%202%2C%20residents%20keep%20track%20of%20their%20birthdays%20on%20a%20large%20chalkboard.%3Cp%3EMaria%20Noyen%2FBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3ELiving%20quarters%20at%20the%20Harlem%20Cohabs%20house%20are%20separated%20into%20%26quot%3Bunits.%26quot%3B%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBetween%20four%20and%20six%20people%20live%20in%20a%20single%20unit%2C%20which%20is%20divided%20into%20several%20bedrooms%2C%20a%20lounge%2C%20and%20a%20kitchen.%20Units%20also%20come%20equipped%20with%20laundry%2C%20a%20prized%20amenity%20not%20every%20New%20Yorker%20can%20say%20they%20have.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETypical%20roommate%20squabbles%20about%20food%20and%20cleanliness%20are%20surprisingly%20rare%2C%20Elisa%20said%2C%20as%20the%20homes%20are%20cleaned%20professionally%20once%20a%20week%20and%20because%20residents%20have%20their%20own%20designated%20shelves%20in%20fridges%20and%20pantries.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe've%20never%20even%20had%20to%20discuss%20that%20because%20everything%20is%20planned%20within%20Cohabs%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAnother%20beauty%20of%20the%20units%2C%20according%20to%20De%20Vroey%2C%20is%20that%20they%20provide%20a%20quieter%20place%20for%20members%20to%20hang%20out%20if%20they%20need%20a%20break%20from%20the%20busier%20common%20spaces.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BYou%20kind%20of%20have%20your%20private%20space%2C%26quot%3B%20De%20Vroey%20said.%20%26quot%3BBut%20then%2C%20when%20you%20want%2C%20you%20can%20always%20go%20and%20see%20everyone%20else.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3EAll%20of%20the%20units%20are%20furnished%2C%20which%20some%20residents%20love.%20They%20can%20also%20find%20ways%20to%20personalize%20the%20space.%20%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%226000%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20kitchen%20in%20one%20of%20the%20units.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F65fc64a82417f97b87ce1de3%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%224000%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EA%20kitchen%20in%20one%20of%20the%20units.%3Cp%3EMaria%20Noyen%2FBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3ELike%20the%20rest%20of%20the%20house%2C%20the%20units%20come%20furnished%20and%20move-in%20ready.%20Clark%20said%20that%20the%20furniture%20is%20mostly%20secondhand%2C%20adding%20%26quot%3Bpersonality%26quot%3B%20and%20color%20to%20the%20living%20spaces.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BYou're%20honestly%20allowed%20to%20bring%20whatever%20you%20want%2C%20but%20everything's%20already%20furnished%2C%20so%20you%20don't%20really%20need%20it%2C%26quot%3B%20De%20Vroey%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20residents%20who%20want%20to%20add%20an%20extra%20personal%20touch%2C%20there%20is%20the%20option%20to%20buy%20furniture%20or%20decorations%20and%20%26quot%3Blet%20loose%26quot%3B%20by%20drawing%20on%20black%20chalkboards%20featured%20in%20the%20common%20space%20in%20each%20unit%2C%20Clark%20said.%20Most%20of%20them%20are%20decorated%20with%20the%20names%20and%20birthdays%20of%20the%20residents.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3EBedrooms%20within%20the%20units%20vary%20in%20size%20and%20price%2C%20and%20some%20are%20set%20up%20to%20accommodate%20couples.%20%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222850%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Some%20rooms%20are%20available%20for%20couples%20to%20share.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F65fc6584895d8220303304aa%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221900%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3ESome%20rooms%20are%20available%20for%20couples%20to%20share.%3Cp%3EPierre%20Jampy%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20Harlem%20house%2C%20a%20few%20rooms%20are%20%26quot%3Bbigger%26quot%3B%20and%20have%20extra%20wardrobes%2C%20desks%2C%20and%20a%20larger%20bed%2C%20to%20accommodate%20couples.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe're%20still%20waiting%20for%20our%20first%20Cohabs%20baby%2C%26quot%3B%20De%20Vroey%20joked.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3EBathrooms%20are%20never%20shared%20by%20more%20than%20three%20residents.%20%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222850%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Bathrooms%20are%20never%20shared%20by%20more%20than%20three%20residents.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F65fc77934af076d3cf927e94%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%223800%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EA%20bathroom%20in%20the%20Cohabs%20Harlem%20house.%3Cp%3EMaria%20Noyen%2FBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EResidents%20who%20don't%20pay%20more%20for%20a%20private%20bathroom%20connected%20to%20their%20bedrooms%20have%20to%20share.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThere%20are%20like%2014%20private%20baths%20within%20this%20house%2C%26quot%3B%20Clark%20said%2C%20adding%20that%20residents%20never%20have%20to%20share%20a%20bathroom%20with%20more%20than%20two%20other%20people.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3ERayon%20pays%20around%20%242%2C000%20a%20month%20for%20a%20room%20in%20Cohabs'%20Harlem%20townhouse.%20%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221280%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Greg's%20only%20living%20experience%20in%20NYC%20has%20been%20through%20Cohabs.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F65fc6649895d822030330539%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22960%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3ERayon's%20only%20living%20experience%20in%20NYC%20has%20been%20in%20Cohabs%20locations.%3Cp%3EMaria%20Noyen%2FBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3ERayon%2C%20a%2036-year-old%20startup%20founder%20from%20Belgium%2C%20moved%20to%20NYC%20in%202023.%20He%20spent%20a%20few%20months%20living%20in%20a%20Cohabs%20location%20in%20Brooklyn%20before%20deciding%20it%20was%20too%20much%20of%20a%20%26quot%3Bparty%20area%26quot%3B%20and%20switching%20to%20the%20Harlem%20house.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBefore%20Cohabs%2C%20Rayon%20had%20never%20lived%20in%20an%20official%20coliving%20space%20before%20but%20had%20spent%20time%20sharing%20a%20house%20with%20six%20other%20friends%20in%20Europe.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThat%20was%20some%20of%20the%20most%20amazing%20years%20of%20my%20life%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ECohabs%2C%20he%20said%2C%20recreates%20that%20experience%20for%20people%20later%20in%20life%20when%20they%20are%20more%20financially%20stable.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BPeople%20go%20to%20university%2C%20they%20get%20their%20job%2C%20they%20settle%20down%2C%20and%20then%20they%20buy%20a%20house%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%20%26quot%3BThey%20kind%20of%20skip%20that%20opportunity%20to%20take%20advantage%20of%20the%20fact%20that%20you're%20no%20longer%20a%20poor%20student.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3ERayon%20thought%20his%20stay%20at%20Cohabs%20would%20be%20short-term%2C%20but%20he's%20open%20to%20living%20there%20for%20a%20longer%20stretch.%20%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%225333%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Residents%20can%20enjoy%20sunny%20days%20in%20NYC%20on%20the%20upstairs%20garden%20patio.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F65fc76a4895d822030330fb2%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%224000%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EResidents%20can%20enjoy%20sunny%20days%20in%20NYC%20on%20the%20upstairs%20patio.%3Cp%3EMaria%20Noyen%2FBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20Rayon%20first%20decided%20to%20live%20in%20a%20Cohabs%20location%2C%20he%20thought%20it%20would%20be%20a%20cool%20place%20to%20live%20for%20a%20few%20months%20and%20meet%20a%20few%20people%20while%20looking%20for%20a%20traditional%20apartment.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENearly%20a%20year%20later%2C%20he's%20still%20living%20in%20a%20Cohabs%20house%20and%20hasn't%20thought%20much%20about%20when%20he'll%20move%20out%2C%20partially%20because%20of%20how%20most%20things%20are%20taken%20care%20of%20for%20him.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20a%20startup%20founder%2C%20he%20said%20he%20prioritizes%20pragmatism%20and%20efficiency%2C%20which%20is%20why%20the%20Cohabs%20lifestyle%20appeals%20to%20him.%20The%20home%20is%20cleaned%20once%20a%20week%20by%20professionals%2C%20there's%20an%20app%20to%20report%20any%20damage%20or%20maintenance%20issues%2C%20and%20the%20lease%20is%20relatively%20flexible.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20don't%20have%20to%20think%20about%20cleaning%20or%20administration%20of%20any%20kind%20whatsoever%20except%20from%20giving%20my%20notice%2C%26quot%3B%20Rayon%20said.%20%26quot%3BThat's%20a%20huge%20mental%20relief.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3ELiving%20in%20a%20Cohabs%20share%20house%20might%20not%20always%20be%20cheaper%20than%20traditional%20apartments%2C%20but%20Rayon%20said%20the%20amenities%20make%20it%20worth%20it.%20%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221167%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Cohabs%20residents%20hanging%20out%20in%20the%20basement.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F65fc76ac4af076d3cf927df7%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22875%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3ECohabs%20residents%20hanging%20out%20in%20the%20basement.%3Cp%3EMaria%20Noyen%2FBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3ERayon%20said%20the%20price%20he%20pays%20to%20live%20with%20Cohabs%20isn't%20necessarily%20cheaper%20than%20a%20traditional%20apartment%20in%20NYC%2C%20but%20he%20doesn't%20mind.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20could%20go%20and%20rent%20out%20my%20own%20studio%20here%20in%20New%20York%2C%20but%20it%20would%20be%20a%20tiny%20shoebox%2C%20and%20then%20I'd%20have%20to%20get%20all%20these%20supplementary%20things%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3EAs%20Gen%20Zers%20and%20millennials%20grapple%20with%20a%20loneliness%20epidemic%2C%20it%20doesn't%20hurt%20that%20Cohabs%20gives%20its%20members%20a%20built-in%20social%20life.%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%224032%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Mail%20boxes%20for%20some%20of%20the%20residents.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F65fc78024af076d3cf927ec2%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%223024%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EMailboxes%20for%20some%20of%20the%20residents.%3Cp%3EMaria%20Noyen%2FBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EAmid%20the%20loneliness%20epidemic%20affecting%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmillennials-gen-z-blame-loneliness-on-housing-affordability-crisis-2023-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EGen%20Zers%20and%20millennials%2C%3C%2Fa%3E%20one%20of%20the%20biggest%20perks%20that%20several%20members%20swear%20by%20is%20that%20Cohabs%20provides%20them%20with%20friends%20the%20moment%20they%20move%20in.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt's%20even%20more%20of%20an%20appeal%20for%20members%20who%20have%20moved%20to%20NYC%20from%20abroad%2C%20including%20Rayon%2C%20Elisa%2C%20and%20De%20Vroey.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20arrived%20in%20the%20US%20on%20the%20second%20of%20July%20last%20year%2C%20and%20like%20two%20days%20later%2C%20it%20was%20the%20Fourth%20of%20July.%20It%20was%20amazing.%20There%20was%20a%20party%20in%20my%20house%2C%26quot%3B%20Rayon%20said.%20%26quot%3BIt%20was%20as%20if%20I%20had%20been%20there%20for%20two%20years.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWhen%20people%20say%20New%20York%20is%20the%20loneliest%20city%20in%20the%20world%2C%20I%20have%20not%20experienced%20that%20at%20all%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20added.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESocial%20events%20occur%20regularly%20across%20each%20Cohabs%20location%20in%20NYC%2C%20and%20all%20members%20are%20invited.%20Residents%20use%20WhatsApp%20groups%20to%20coordinate%20events%20like%20Super%20Bowl%20or%20Christmas%20parties%2C%20which%20help%20foster%20a%20tight-knit%20%26quot%3Bbond%26quot%3B%20between%20residents%2C%20whether%20they're%20in%20their%20early%2020s%20or%20their%20late%2030s%2C%20De%20Vroey%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EElisa%20said%20informal%20dinners%20are%20a%20%26quot%3Blove%20language%26quot%3B%20among%20members.%20%26quot%3BEvery%20Sunday%20last%20year%20during%20summer%2C%20we%20were%20cooking%20amazing%20dinners%20for%20everyone%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3EClark%20said%20some%20Cohabs%20residents%20stay%20for%20long%20periods%20of%20time.%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%223313%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Dan%20Clark%20is%20the%20managing%20director%20of%20Cohabs%20in%20the%20US.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F65f9fbbd4af076d3cf91ced8%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%222485%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EDan%20Clark%20is%20the%20managing%20director%20of%20Cohabs%20in%20the%20US.%3Cp%3EMaria%20Noyen%2FBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EClark%20said%20Cohabs%20isn't%20interested%20in%20filling%20up%20houses%20with%20residents%20interested%20in%20only%20staying%20a%20few%20months.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThis%20is%20not%20transient%20housing%2C%20to%20be%20crystal%20clear%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said%2C%20adding%20that%20the%20average%20person%20lives%20in%20a%20Cohabs%20share%20house%20for%2011%20months%20at%20a%20time.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EClark%20said%20another%20thing%20that%20helps%20set%20the%20company%20apart%20is%20that%20Cohabs%20has%20a%20strategy%20to%20%26quot%3Bbuy%20and%20hold%20the%20assets%2C%26quot%3B%20meaning%20that%20the%20company%20owns%20its%20buildings%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Eand%20can%20%26quot%3Bpocket%26quot%3B%20cash%20to%20invest%20back%20into%20creating%20a%20real%20home%20for%20its%20members.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3ECohabs%20may%20have%20fans%20in%20NYC%2C%20but%20it%20might%20need%20to%20tweak%20its%20model%20to%20expand%20across%20the%20US.%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221280%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Ya%C3%ABlle%20De%20Vroey%20works%20for%20Cohabs%20and%20lives%20in%20one%20of%20the%20locations%20in%20Harlem.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F660b14e41caec1275a6b9774%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22953%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EYa%C3%ABlle%20De%20Vroey%2C%20who%20works%20for%20Cohabs%20and%20lives%20in%20one%20of%20the%20locations%20in%20Harlem%2C%20has%20the%20company's%20logo%20tattooed%20on%20her%20ankle.%3Cp%3EMaria%20Noyen%2FBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EPart%20of%20the%20reason%20Cohabs'%20attempt%20to%20enter%20the%20US%20market%20has%20been%20successful%20so%20far%20is%20because%20it%20began%20operations%20in%20NYC%2C%20Clark%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMany%20people%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmoving-to-new-york-city-nyc-weather-expensive-jersey-city-2024-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Emoving%20to%20the%20city%3C%2Fa%3E%20are%20younger%20and%20unmarried%2C%20the%20prime%20target%20audience%20for%20a%20coliving%20concept%20like%20Cohabs%2C%20Clark%20added.%20It's%20also%20a%20hub%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.nyc.gov%2Fsite%2Finternationalbusiness%2Fwhy-nyc%2Fa-diverse-global-city.page%23%3A~%3Atext%3DOver%2520three%2520million%2520New%2520Yorkers%2Cbusinesses%2520are%2520owned%2520by%2520immigrants.%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Efor%20international%20residents%3C%2Fa%3E%20%E2%80%94%20many%20of%20whom%20move%20to%20NYC%20alone%20and%20seek%20a%20sense%20of%20belonging.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20to%20replicate%20Cohabs'%20success%20elsewhere%20in%20the%20US%2C%20Clark%20said%20the%20company%20might%20have%20to%20consider%20tweaking%20the%20model%20to%20accommodate%20other%20aspects%20of%20American%20culture.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BAs%20we%20go%20into%20new%20markets%20where%20there's%20less%20and%20less%20of%20an%20international%20vibe%2C%20we're%20going%20to%20have%20to%20be%20more%20sensitive%20to%20what%20is%20more%20palatable%20to%20Americans%20in%20general%2C%26quot%3B%20Clark%20said.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOne%20of%20the%20ways%20Cohabs%20is%20considering%20doing%20that%20is%20through%20smaller%20coliving%20spaces%20that%20more%20closely%20resemble%20a%20traditional%20housing%20model%20%E2%80%94%20spaces%20shared%20by%20six%20to%20eight%20people%20instead%20of%20nearly%2030.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20that%20way%2C%20%26quot%3Bpeople%20can%20still%20get%20to%20know%20each%20other%20and%20form%20really%20strong%20bonds%26quot%3B%20without%20it%20being%20%26quot%3Boverwhelming%2C%26quot%3B%20Clark%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20several%20residents%20of%20the%20Harlem%20house%2C%20including%20De%20Vroey%2C%20the%20experience%20has%20been%20so%20positive%20that%20they've%20immortalized%20it%20with%20matching%20Cohabs-themed%20tattoos.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20suits%20her%20in%20a%20way%20that%20a%20traditional%20roommate%20setup%20might%20not.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIf%20you%20were%20in%20a%20smaller%20apartment%20or%20in%20a%20smaller%20house%2C%20you%20would%20want%20to%20get%20out%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3