aste-video%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E14th-century%20recipe%3C%2Fa%3E%20highlighted%20how%20it%20blended%20well%20with%20wheat%20flour%2C%20almonds%2C%20eggs%20and%20sugar.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EA%201770%20American%20cookbook%20%E2%80%98The%20Art%20of%20Cookery%E2%80%99%20spoke%20of%20how%20the%20vermicelli%20made%20an%20excellent%20meal%20when%20blended%20well%20with%20egg%20yolks%20and%20flour.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAsian%20cuisine%20embraced%20vermicelli%20and%20its%20many%20forms%20right%20since%20the%20Qin%20dynasty%20dating%20back%20to%20221%20BCE%3B%20whether%20as%20%3Cem%3Emi%20fen%3C%2Fem%3E%20(rice%20noodles)%2C%20or%20%3Cem%3Emung%20bean%20vermicelli%3C%2Fem%3E%20(cellophane%20or%20glass%20noodles)%2C%20or%20%3Cem%3Emisua%3C%2Fem%3E%20(wheat-based%20vermicelli).%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EComing%20to%20the%20Indian%20variations%20of%20vermicelli%2C%20local%20lore%20tells%20us%20that%20the%20only%20way%20perhaps%20that%20vermicelli%20made%20its%20way%20into%20the%20subcontinent%20is%20through%20trade%20networks%20extending%20between%20the%20Middle%20East%20and%20India.%20In%20fact%2C%20in%20Egypt%2C%20the%20technique%20of%20frying%20vermicelli%20(%3Cem%3Eshe%E2%80%99reya%3C%2Fem%3E)%20in%20butter%20or%20oil%20was%20prevalent.%20Once%20fried%2C%20water%20would%20be%20added%20to%20the%20fried%20noodles%20and%20it%20would%20be%20cooked%20with%20rice.%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thebetterindia.com%2F261268%2Fbiryani-map-of-india-taste-the-history-find-your-favourite-among-28-versions%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EA%20hearty%20meal%3C%2Fa%3E!%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAn%20article%20in%20the%C2%A0%3Cem%3EDeccan%20Herald%3C%2Fem%3E%C2%A0explores%20the%20origins%20of%20the%20sweet%20dish.%20Hand%20rolling%20of%C2%A0%3Cem%3Eseviyan%2C%C2%A0%3C%2Fem%3Ewhich%20was%20once%20a%20traditional%20occupation%2C%20gained%20popularity%20during%20the%20time%20of%20the%20Mughal%20rule.%20In%20fact%2C%20it%20is%20said%20that%20Emperor%20Humayun%20ignited%20the%20love%20for%C2%A0%3Cem%3Eseviyan%3C%2Fem%3E%C2%A0in%20the%20court%20by%20reintroducing%20the%20Persian%C2%A0%3Cem%3Ekurma%3C%2Fem%3E%C2%A0as%C2%A0%3Cem%3Edum%20ki%20seviyan.%20%3C%2Fem%3EBut%2C%20it%20was%C2%A0Emperor%20Shah%20Jahan%20who%20was%20instrumental%20in%20the%20dish%20becoming%20its%20current%20version%20with%20spices%2C%20ghee%20and%20dry%20fruits.%20An%20anecdote%20often%20told%20is%20how%20the%20Emperor%20requested%20a%20special%20sunset-coloured%C2%A0%3Cem%3Evarq%3C%2Fem%3E%C2%A0(an%20edible%20foil%20garnishing)%20to%20accompany%20the%C2%A0%3Cem%3Eseviyan%3C%2Fem%3E.%20This%20tradition%20lasted%20until%20the%20time%20of%20Bahadur%20Shah%20Zafar%20who%20would%20prepare%20his%C2%A0%3Cem%3Eseviyan%3C%2Fem%3E%C2%A0by%20hand.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOnce%20the%20ingredient%20entered%20India%2C%20it%20was%20local%20palate%20preferences%20that%20gave%20birth%20to%20the%20many%20vermicelli-based%20dishes%20that%20now%20exist.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20%E2%80%98Oxford%20Companion%20to%20Food%E2%80%99%20by%20Alan%20Davidson%20and%20Tom%20Jaine%2C%20says%20the%20following%20about%20%3Cem%3Eseviyan%3C%2Fem%3E%3A%20The%20Sanskrit%20name%20for%20noodles%20is%20%3Cem%3Esevika%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20which%20may%20derive%20from%20an%20unrecorded%20word%20meaning%20thread%20connected%20with%20the%20root%20%3Cem%3Esiv%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20which%20refers%20to%20sewing.%20%3Cem%3ESev%3C%2Fem%3E%20are%20crisp%20fried%20noodles%20prepared%20from%20%3Cem%3Ebesan%3C%2Fem%3E%20(chickpea)%20flour.%20%3Cem%3ESeviyan%3C%2Fem%3E%20(also%20%3Cem%3Eseviya%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20%3Cem%3Esivayya%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20%3Cem%3Eshavayi%3C%2Fem%3E)%20usually%20refers%20to%20a%20sweet%20dish%20of%20vermicelli%20noodles.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-image%5C%22%3E%5Cn%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20637px)%20100vw%2C%20637px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F04%2FScreenshot-2024-04-08-190920-17